01:07:01.860 --> 01:07:03.060 align:middle line:90%
really, really like.

01:07:03.060 --> 01:07:07.400 align:middle line:90%


01:07:07.400 --> 01:07:10.140 align:middle line:84%
It's a little bit
like improv theater.

01:07:10.140 --> 01:07:12.690 align:middle line:84%
You know how they say that
improv is so good for getting

01:07:12.690 --> 01:07:13.970 align:middle line:90%
rid of anxiety?

01:07:13.970 --> 01:07:18.060 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're on stage
doing like an improv troupe,

01:07:18.060 --> 01:07:19.980 align:middle line:84%
it's like, OK,
here's the setting.

01:07:19.980 --> 01:07:21.480 align:middle line:90%
Here's the situation.

01:07:21.480 --> 01:07:22.320 align:middle line:90%
Go.

01:07:22.320 --> 01:07:24.870 align:middle line:84%
And once they say go, well,
now you're in the present.

01:07:24.870 --> 01:07:26.560 align:middle line:90%
Now, you are in it.

01:07:26.560 --> 01:07:28.980 align:middle line:84%
And so I always say when
you're creating an experience,

01:07:28.980 --> 01:07:30.160 align:middle line:84%
it's like you're
picking the location.

01:07:30.160 --> 01:07:31.500 align:middle line:84%
It means you're
setting the stage.

01:07:31.500 --> 01:07:32.880 align:middle line:84%
You're window-dressing
the stage.

01:07:32.880 --> 01:07:34.830 align:middle line:84%
Because once you hit go
and you're in the present,

01:07:34.830 --> 01:07:35.790 align:middle line:84%
that stage is going
to be where you're

01:07:35.790 --> 01:07:37.180 align:middle line:90%
going to be interacting with.

01:07:37.180 --> 01:07:37.980 align:middle line:90%
So pick a place.

01:07:37.980 --> 01:07:39.143 align:middle line:90%
And then pick the people.

01:07:39.143 --> 01:07:40.560 align:middle line:84%
It's the ingredients
in the salad.

01:07:40.560 --> 01:07:42.450 align:middle line:84%
Because once you get
stoned, those people

01:07:42.450 --> 01:07:45.930 align:middle line:84%
are going to now infuse
into your experience.

01:07:45.930 --> 01:07:48.750 align:middle line:84%
Somebody once said that cannabis
intoxication is a fusion

01:07:48.750 --> 01:07:50.220 align:middle line:90%
of cognition and dream.

01:07:50.220 --> 01:07:52.320 align:middle line:84%
So I often think of
the film "Inception,"

01:07:52.320 --> 01:07:53.790 align:middle line:90%
like when they're dreaming.

01:07:53.790 --> 01:07:56.220 align:middle line:84%
If they're dreaming
in the real world.

01:07:56.220 --> 01:07:58.278 align:middle line:84%
And then in layer one,
they're like whatever,

01:07:58.278 --> 01:07:59.820 align:middle line:84%
having something
happen in the dream.

01:07:59.820 --> 01:08:01.590 align:middle line:84%
In the real world, you
pour water on them.

01:08:01.590 --> 01:08:03.760 align:middle line:84%
And in the dream world,
it starts to rain.

01:08:03.760 --> 01:08:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of what
happens when you're high.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:08.208 align:middle line:84%
Whatever you've preplanned
and the people that you're

01:08:08.208 --> 01:08:10.470 align:middle line:84%
with-- once you enter
that altered states,

01:08:10.470 --> 01:08:14.580 align:middle line:84%
all those things are going to
infuse into the waking dream

01:08:14.580 --> 01:08:17.939 align:middle line:84%
that you're having into,
quote unquote, "your trip."

01:08:17.939 --> 01:08:20.010 align:middle line:84%
And so that's very
important that you

01:08:20.010 --> 01:08:23.040 align:middle line:84%
plan the context in which
you're going to submit.

01:08:23.040 --> 01:08:25.770 align:middle line:84%
Because at some point,
you have to submit, right?

01:08:25.770 --> 01:08:28.077 align:middle line:84%
And I think it was
Robert Moore who said,

01:08:28.077 --> 01:08:29.660 align:middle line:84%
"If you cannot submit,
you cannot die.

01:08:29.660 --> 01:08:31.620 align:middle line:84%
If you cannot die,
you cannot be reborn."

01:08:31.620 --> 01:08:34.260 align:middle line:84%
But he's talking about a
psychological surrendering

01:08:34.260 --> 01:08:37.140 align:middle line:84%
into the moment, the bliss
crucifixion, as our friend,

01:08:37.140 --> 01:08:39.490 align:middle line:90%
Jamie Wheal likes to say.

01:08:39.490 --> 01:08:41.399 align:middle line:90%
So, yeah.

01:08:41.399 --> 01:08:42.870 align:middle line:90%
I think it's about curation.

