01:15:20.510 --> 01:15:22.100 align:middle line:90%
It's already deep into the arts.

01:15:22.100 --> 01:15:24.200 align:middle line:90%
This is human performance.

01:15:24.200 --> 01:15:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And an accelerated-- one of
the most interesting things

01:15:27.320 --> 01:15:29.858 align:middle line:84%
about flow is that
if you're going

01:15:29.858 --> 01:15:31.400 align:middle line:84%
to keep pace in an
exponential world,

01:15:31.400 --> 01:15:32.550 align:middle line:90%
you need to do two things.

01:15:32.550 --> 01:15:34.340 align:middle line:84%
You need to move at
speed, and you need

01:15:34.340 --> 01:15:35.600 align:middle line:90%
to be able to think at scale.

01:15:35.600 --> 01:15:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And as Jason pointed
out, the human brain

01:15:37.880 --> 01:15:39.170 align:middle line:90%
doesn't think at scale, right?

01:15:39.170 --> 01:15:42.670 align:middle line:84%
We literally cannot
process exponential change.

01:15:42.670 --> 01:15:44.810 align:middle line:90%
In flow, we can.

01:15:44.810 --> 01:15:45.950 align:middle line:90%
Everything speeds up.

01:15:45.950 --> 01:15:47.630 align:middle line:84%
Literally, the brain's
pattern recognition-- we take

01:15:47.630 --> 01:15:48.922 align:middle line:90%
in more information per second.

01:15:48.922 --> 01:15:50.430 align:middle line:90%
We process this more quickly.

01:15:50.430 --> 01:15:53.490 align:middle line:84%
So we can-- that's how our
brains can think in this world.

01:15:53.490 --> 01:15:55.430 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's going
to be fundamental.

01:15:55.430 --> 01:15:57.508 align:middle line:84%
If we're going to see
50 years from now,

01:15:57.508 --> 01:15:58.550 align:middle line:90%
we're going to need this.

01:15:58.550 --> 01:16:00.980 align:middle line:84%
The other thing that's
interesting about flow

01:16:00.980 --> 01:16:03.350 align:middle line:90%
