01:16:03.350 --> 01:16:08.790 align:middle line:84%
But it does tend to produce
more empathy over time,

01:16:08.790 --> 01:16:12.390 align:middle line:84%
especially expanding it
into the natural world.

01:16:12.390 --> 01:16:16.070 align:middle line:84%
So it expand-- the flow tends
to not only increase empathy.

01:16:16.070 --> 01:16:18.650 align:middle line:84%
It tends to expand
the line of empathy

01:16:18.650 --> 01:16:21.140 align:middle line:84%
often beyond the border of
species, which is the biggest--

01:16:21.140 --> 01:16:23.950 align:middle line:84%
one of the reasons we're in a
giant environmental crisis is

01:16:23.950 --> 01:16:25.280 align:middle line:90%
it's not empathy for all.

01:16:25.280 --> 01:16:27.930 align:middle line:84%
It's empathy for
humans, perhaps,

01:16:27.930 --> 01:16:29.030 align:middle line:90%
but we don't see plants.

01:16:29.030 --> 01:16:29.990 align:middle line:90%
We don't see animals.

01:16:29.990 --> 01:16:31.620 align:middle line:90%
We don't see ecosystems.

01:16:31.620 --> 01:16:33.650 align:middle line:84%
So we don't realize
that we're in the middle

01:16:33.650 --> 01:16:35.150 align:middle line:90%
of the sixth great extinction.

